The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.

Unable to hear, speak, or wield a sword, Prince Bojji doesn’t seem like a typical heir to the throne—and his kingdom agrees. But his fateful encounter with Kage, a shadow on the ground, gives him his first true friend. The two set off on a grand adventure and, together, form a bond that can overcome any obstacle...even being king.
(Source: Funimation)
Youkya na Kanojo wa Kyorikan ga Bug tte Iru: Deatte Soku wo Mochikaeri Shicha Damenano?
Hokenshitsu no Otona na Senpai, Ore no Maede wa Sugu Dereru

Yuzuki, a senior member of the school infirmary committee, has a gentle and mature demeanor. Kyoji, a regular in the infirmary, got to know her as she teased him every day. He wanted to get back at her, so he said, "I like you..." When Yuzuki heard that, her behavior went haywire!?
(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
